<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3915.3.7>
    bibo:endPage "432" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "423" ;
    bibo:volume "3915" ;
    dc:creator "Heard, Richard W.; Vargas, Rita" ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Cyathura odaliscae, a new species of anthurid isopod (Crustacea: Peracarida) from a brackish habitat on the Pacific coast of Costa Rica" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233056>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233057>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233058>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233059>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233060> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233056>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Cyathura odaliscae, n. sp. Non-incubatory female [A – D, F, I]; adult male [E, G – H, J – K]: A, antenna 1 [= antennula], distal aspect; B, antenna 2 [= antenna], distal aspect; C, D, habitus, lateral and dorsal aspects, respectively; E, antenna 1, distal articles showing cluster of aesthetascs; F, right pleopod 1; G, right pleopod 2 with copulatory stylet (appendix masculina); H, enlargement of distal end of copulatory stylet; I, anterior part of head; J, uropod; K, telson, dorsal aspect. Scale for C and D = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/233056/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233057>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Cyathura odaliscae n. sp. Antenna 2 of adult male (length 5.1 mm). A, entire, dorsal aspect; B, articles 1 and 2 ventral aspect." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/233057/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233058>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Cyathura odaliscae n. sp. Adult male (length 5.1 mm). A, left mandible; B, lamina dentate; C, first maxilla; D, tip of first maxilla, another aspect of dentition; E, maxilliped; F, pereopod 1 inner aspect palm (propodus) and dactylus with enlargement of inner margin of propodus; G, pereopod 1 showing setation of merus, carpus, propodus; H, pereopod 1 lateral view (setae) omitted; I, pereopod 1 inner view (setae omitted except for “ comb-row on distoventral margin of propodus)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/233058/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233059>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Cyathura odaliscae, n. sp. Adult male pereopods 2 – 6, A – F, respectively; F, with enlargement of dactylus, propodus, and distal part of carpus for pereopod 7." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/233059/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.233060>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Tips of the male copulatory stylets for 22 of the 32 species currently included within the genus Cyathura sensu Poore 2001. A, C. esquivel; B, C. profunda; C, C. bentotae; D, C. munda; E, C. cubana; F, C. rudloei; G, C. shanghaiensis; H, C. indica; I, C. terryae; J, C. hakea; K, C. bruguiera; L, C. furcata; M, C. sagamiensis; N, C. muromiensis; O, C. kikuchii; P, C. shinjikoensis; Q, C. higoensis; R ,, C. carinata; S, C. burbancki; T, C. madelinae; U, C. polita; V, C. odaliscae, n. sp. Figures A – U modified from: Kensley et al. 1997 (A); Kensley 1980, 1982, 1987 (B, F, & H), respectively); Lui et al. 2013 (G); Müller 1990, 1991 (I & C, respectively); Poore & Lew Ton 1985 (J & K, respectively); Menzies 1951 (D); Negoescu 1981 (E); Nunomura 1974, 2001, 2006 (N, P, M, respectively); Nunomura 1977 (O & Q, respectively); Nunomura & Hagino 2000 (L); Frankenberg 1965 (S), Miller & Burbank 1961 (R, U, respectively); Hackney & Ganucheau 1989 (T)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/233060/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

